      "role": "user",
      "content": "i tried changing the width to 30% like u said but it didnt really fix the overlap, the image is still sitting right on top of the text for some reason. the float might be messing with it too. if i remove the float, do u think i should use flexbox or just a different margin setting to make sure the text stays below the image on mobile?",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "i tried changing the width to 30% like u said but it didnt really fix the overlap, the image is still sitting right on top of the text for some reason. the float might be messing with it too. if i remove the float, do u think i should use flexbox or just a different margin setting to make sure the text stays below the image on mobile?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Removing the float and using flexbox could indeed help solve the overlapping issue. Flexbox is great for laying out items in a row or column and can give you more control over the alignment and spacing of your elements. Try using the following code snippet to replace the float with flexbox:\n\n```css\n@media only screen and (max-width: 749px) {\n  .product-single__media {\n    display: flex;\n    width: 30%;\n    justify-content: flex-start; /* Aligns the image to the start of the container */\n  }\n\n  .product-single__title {\n    margin-top: 10px; /* Adjust the margin to ensure the title is below the image */\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis should help keep your product image and title neatly stacked, with the title text nicely below the image on mobile devices. Good luck with your Shopify theme!",
      "source": "target",
